Task 4
1. Script to install nginx or httpd

2. When the user run the script, it should print options to select which software to installation

Eg.
1. httpd
2. nginx

User select 1 or 2

Then script should continue, check whether package is already installed if not install.

Note: The same script should work in Ubuntu as well as CentOS

For you reference, the in Ubuntu the package name is httpd, in CentOS it's apache2.
Add condition to check which operating system it is and select httpd or apache2. Checking of which operating system should be checked within script 

Use functions whenever possible
